metadata.title: Why Cannot I Connect With CS+ With FSG in Workbench6?

sections.content:
Question:
In the Workbench6 First Step Guide, I get a "Target MCU and MCU on target board does not match" error and I can't connect to CS+. What could be the problem?
Answer:
The possible causes are as follows:
External power is not supplied
Clock setting is incorrect
CPU product name is wrong
Workbench6 is now in maintenance status, and we do not plan to update it in the future.
Use QE for Capacitive Touch as a support tool for developing a modern capacitive touch sensor.
QE for Capacitive Touch can be downloaded from URL below.
https://www.renesas.com/qe-capacitive-touch
  Suitable Products
RX113
RX130
RX231, RX230
